[3] Selected media reports of transmission outside of China
A. 3 more 2019-nCoV positive on cruise ship
Date: Fri 7 Feb 2020
Source: NHK [in Japanese, machine trans., edited]
https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200208/k10012277911000.html?utm_int=all_contents_just-in_001


On the cruise ship Diamond Princess, on which an outbreak of the new coronavirus has been confirmed, 3 new cases have been confirmed. Since the cruise ship anchored off the port of Yokohama, 64 passengers and crew members have been infected.

The Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare has conducted a quarantine of about 3700 passengers and all crew members on the Diamond Princess this month [February 2020], including those with symptoms such as fever and cough. We have collected samples from a total of 279 people who have been in close contact with each other and have performed virus tests.

On [8 Feb 2020], 6 new results were completed, and 3 infections were confirmed. The 3 newly confirmed infections have been transported to medical institutions and hospitalized.

The cruise ship left Yokohama last month [January 2020], after which an 80 year old man living in Hong Kong was found infected with the new coronavirus after leaving the ship in Hong Kong.

The total number of confirmed cruise ship passengers infected, excluding the man from Hong Kong, is 64. Also, according to the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare, 1 of those infected by [6 Feb 2020] had some form of chronic illness and has severe symptoms.

The Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare has requested that the remaining 3600 passengers and crew members remain on board, and in principle, wait 14 days from [5 Feb 2020] in their cabin.

The number of people infected with the new coronavirus in Japan is 89, including 64 on the cruise ship.

